Class ApplicationConfig

java.lang.Object
org.jscience.server.config.ApplicationConfig
public class ApplicationConfig extends Object
Central configuration management for JScience Server. Loads configuration from multiple sources with the following priority: 1. Environment variables (highest priority) 2. System properties 3. application.properties file (lowest priority) Usage: 
ApplicationConfig config = ApplicationConfig.getInstance();
int port = config.getGrpcPort();
String mlflowUri = config.getMlflowUri();
Since:
1.0
Author:
Silvere Martin-Michiellot, Gemini AI (Google DeepMind)
